Headlines.Author: Bob Tita
Headlines.Headline: US Boat Industry No Longer Floundering But Recovery Murky

PARAGRAPH.#text: The U.S. recreational boat industry has likely stopped sinking, but it faces a slow recovery and an unpredictable future. Sales of recreational power boats fell to a record low of 132,000 vessels last year, a 55% decline from 2006 and down 14% from 2009. While the industry is widely seen as having bottomed out last year, the momentum behind an upturn remains unclear. Some projections have sales rising as much as 10% this year, but few forecasters are willing to say when or if sales will ever return to the 300,000 boats a year the industry averaged in the 14 years prior to 2007.
